#. <section class="sutta" id="an5.179"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.179:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.179:0.2"
msgid "18. Upāsakavagga"
msgstr "18. A Lay Follower"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an5.179:0.3"
msgid "179. Gihisutta"
msgstr "179. A Layperson"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an5.179:1.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati pañcamattehi upāsakasatehi parivuto yena "
"bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ "
"nisīdi."
msgstr ""
"Then the householder Anāthapiṇḍika, escorted by around five hundred lay "
"followers, went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side."

msgctxt "an5.179:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then the Buddha said to Venerable Sāriputta:"

#. VAR: yaṃ kañci → yaṃ kiñci (bj) | yaṅkiñci (s1-3)
msgctxt "an5.179:1.3"
msgid ""
"“yaṃ kañci, sāriputta, jāneyyātha gihiṃ odātavasanaṃ pañcasu sikkhāpadesu "
"saṃvutakammantaṃ catunnaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ "
"nikāmalābhiṃ akicchalābhiṃ akasiralābhiṃ, so ākaṅkhamāno attanāva attānaṃ "
"byākareyya:"
msgstr ""
"“You should know this, Sāriputta, about those white-clothed laypeople whose "
"actions are restrained in the five precepts, and who get four blissful "
"meditations in the present life belonging to the higher mind when they want, "
"without trouble or difficulty. They may, if they wish, declare of themselves:"

msgctxt "an5.179:1.4"
msgid ""
"‘khīṇanirayomhi khīṇatiracchānayoni khīṇapettivisayo "
"khīṇāpāyaduggativinipāto, sotāpannohamasmi avinipātadhammo niyato "
"sambodhiparāyaṇo’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘I’ve finished with rebirth in hell, the animal realm, and the ghost realm. "
"I’ve finished with all places of loss, bad places, the underworld. I am a "
"stream-enterer! I’m not liable to be reborn in the underworld, and am bound "
"for awakening.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.212"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an5.179:2.1"
msgid "Katamesu pañcasu sikkhāpadesu saṃvutakammanto hoti?"
msgstr "And what are the five precepts in which their actions are restrained?"

msgctxt "an5.179:2.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, sāriputta, ariyasāvako pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti, adinnādānā "
"paṭivirato hoti, kāmesumicchācārā paṭivirato hoti, musāvādā paṭivirato hoti, "
"surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānā paṭivirato hoti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a noble disciple doesn’t kill living creatures, steal, commit "
"sexual misconduct, lie, or use alcoholic drinks that cause negligence."

msgctxt "an5.179:2.3"
msgid "Imesu pañcasu sikkhāpadesu saṃvutakammanto hoti."
msgstr "These are the five precepts in which their actions are restrained."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an5.179:3.1"
msgid ""
"Katamesaṃ catunnaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ nikāmalābhī "
"hoti akicchalābhī akasiralābhī?"
msgstr ""
"And what are the four blissful meditations in the present life belonging to "
"the higher mind that they get when they want, without trouble or difficulty?"

msgctxt "an5.179:3.2"
msgid "Idha, sāriputta, ariyasāvako buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti:"
msgstr "It’s when a noble disciple has experiential confidence in the Buddha:"

msgctxt "an5.179:3.3"
msgid ""
"‘itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū "
"anuttaro purisadammasārathi, satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in "
"knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those "
"who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’"

msgctxt "an5.179:3.4"
msgid ""
"Ayamassa paṭhamo ābhicetasiko diṭṭhadhammasukhavihāro adhigato hoti "
"avisuddhassa cittassa visuddhiyā apariyodātassa cittassa pariyodapanāya."
msgstr ""
"This is the first blissful meditation in the present life belonging to the "
"higher mind, which they achieve in order to purify the unpurified mind and "
"cleanse the unclean mind."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an5.179:4.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, sāriputta, ariyasāvako dhamme aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti:"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a noble disciple has experiential confidence in the teaching:"

msgctxt "an5.179:4.2"
msgid ""
"‘svākkhāto bhagavatā dhammo sandiṭṭhiko akāliko ehipassiko opaneyyiko "
"paccattaṃ veditabbo viññūhī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘The teaching is well explained by the Buddha—realizable in this very life, "
"immediately effective, inviting inspection, relevant, so that sensible "
"people can know it for themselves.’"

msgctxt "an5.179:4.3"
msgid ""
"Ayamassa dutiyo ābhicetasiko diṭṭhadhammasukhavihāro adhigato hoti "
"avisuddhassa cittassa visuddhiyā apariyodātassa cittassa pariyodapanāya."
msgstr "This is the second blissful meditation …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.213"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an5.179:5.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, sāriputta, ariyasāvako saṅghe aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti:"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a noble disciple has experiential confidence in the Saṅgha:"

msgctxt "an5.179:5.2"
msgid ""
"‘suppaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho ujuppaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho "
"ñāyappaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho sāmīcippaṭipanno bhagavato "
"sāvakasaṅgho, yadidaṃ cattāri purisayugāni aṭṭha purisapuggalā esa bhagavato "
"sāvakasaṅgho āhuneyyo pāhuneyyo dakkhiṇeyyo añjalikaraṇīyo anuttaraṃ "
"puññakkhettaṃ lokassā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘The Saṅgha of the Buddha’s disciples is practicing the way that’s good, "
"straightforward, methodical, and proper. It consists of the four pairs, the "
"eight individuals. This Saṅgha of the Buddha’s disciples is worthy of "
"offerings dedicated to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a teacher’"
"s offering, and worthy of greeting with joined palms. It is a supreme field "
"of merit for the world.’"

msgctxt "an5.179:5.3"
msgid ""
"Ayamassa tatiyo ābhicetasiko diṭṭhadhammasukhavihāro adhigato hoti "
"avisuddhassa cittassa visuddhiyā apariyodātassa cittassa pariyodapanāya."
msgstr "This is the third blissful meditation …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an5.179:6.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, sāriputta, ariyasāvako ariyakantehi sīlehi samannāgato hoti "
"akhaṇḍehi acchiddehi asabalehi akammāsehi bhujissehi viññuppasatthehi "
"aparāmaṭṭhehi samādhisaṃvattanikehi."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a noble disciple’s ethical conduct is loved by the noble ones, "
"unbroken, unflawed, unblemished, untainted, liberating, praised by sensible "
"people, not mistaken, and leading to immersion."

msgctxt "an5.179:6.2"
msgid ""
"Ayamassa catuttho ābhicetasiko diṭṭhadhammasukhavihāro adhigato hoti "
"avisuddhassa cittassa visuddhiyā apariyodātassa cittassa pariyodapanāya."
msgstr ""
"This is the fourth blissful meditation in the present life belonging to the "
"higher mind, which they achieve in order to purify the unpurified mind and "
"cleanse the unclean mind."

msgctxt "an5.179:6.3"
msgid ""
"Imesaṃ catunnaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ nikāmalābhī hoti "
"akicchalābhī akasiralābhī."
msgstr ""
"These are the four blissful meditations in the present life belonging to the "
"higher mind that they get when they want, without trouble or difficulty."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an5.179:7.1"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ kañci, sāriputta, jāneyyātha gihiṃ odātavasanaṃ—imesu pañcasu "
"sikkhāpadesu saṃvutakammantaṃ, imesañca catunnaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ "
"diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ nikāmalābhiṃ akicchalābhiṃ akasiralābhiṃ, so "
"ākaṅkhamāno attanāva attānaṃ byākareyya:"
msgstr ""
"You should know this, Sāriputta, about those white-clothed laypeople whose "
"actions are restrained in the five precepts, and who get four blissful "
"meditations in the present life belonging to the higher mind when they want, "
"without trouble or difficulty. They may, if they wish, declare of themselves:"

msgctxt "an5.179:7.2"
msgid ""
"‘khīṇanirayomhi khīṇatiracchānayoni khīṇapettivisayo "
"khīṇāpāyaduggativinipāto, sotāpannohamasmi avinipātadhammo niyato "
"sambodhiparāyaṇo’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘I’ve finished with rebirth in hell, the animal realm, and the ghost realm. "
"I’ve finished with all places of loss, bad places, the underworld. I am a "
"stream-enterer! I’m not liable to be reborn in the underworld, and am bound "
"for awakening.’"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an5.179:8.1"
msgid "Nirayesu bhayaṃ disvā,"
msgstr "Seeing the peril in the hells,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.179:8.2"
msgid "pāpāni parivajjaye;"
msgstr "you should shun bad deeds."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.179:8.3"
msgid "Ariyadhammaṃ samādāya,"
msgstr "Taking up the noble teaching,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.179:8.4"
msgid "paṇḍito parivajjaye."
msgstr "an astute person should shun them."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "an5.179:9.1"
msgid "Na hiṃse pāṇabhūtāni,"
msgstr "You shouldn’t harm living beings,"

# Lit: “while exertion exists”. I think the point is that we can’t help harming invisible creatures, and unlike Jains, don’t try to do the impossible. BB applies this line to the whole verse, but I think this is a mistake. We can’t help unintentionally killing, but normally there is, by definition, no unintentional stealing or lying.
#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.179:9.2"
msgid "vijjamāne parakkame;"
msgstr "as far as that’s possible to do."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.179:9.3"
msgid "Musā ca na bhaṇe jānaṃ,"
msgstr "Nor should you knowingly speak falsehood,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.179:9.4"
msgid "adinnaṃ na parāmase."
msgstr "or take what is not given."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "an5.179:10.1"
msgid "Sehi dārehi santuṭṭho,"
msgstr "Content with your own partners,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: ārame → nārame (bj, s1-3)
msgctxt "an5.179:10.2"
msgid "paradārañca ārame;"
msgstr "you should stay away from the partners of others."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.179:10.3"
msgid "Merayaṃ vāruṇiṃ jantu,"
msgstr "A man shouldn’t drink liquor or wine,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.179:10.4"
msgid "na pive cittamohaniṃ."
msgstr "as they confuse the mind."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "an5.179:11.1"
msgid "Anussareyya sambuddhaṃ,"
msgstr "You should recollect the Buddha,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.179:11.2"
msgid "dhammañcānuvitakkaye;"
msgstr "and reflect on the teaching."

#. <br>
#. VAR: Abyāpajjaṃ → abyāpajjhaṃ (bj, s1-3, mr) | avyāpajjhaṃ (pts1) | abyābajjhaṃ (?)
msgctxt "an5.179:11.3"
msgid "Abyāpajjaṃ hitaṃ cittaṃ,"
msgstr "You should develop a harmless mind of welfare,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.179:11.4"
msgid "devalokāya bhāvaye."
msgstr "which leads to the realms of gods."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "an5.179:12.1"
msgid "Upaṭṭhite deyyadhamme,"
msgstr "When suitable gifts to give are available"

#. <br>
#. VAR: jigīsato → jigiṃsato (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an5.179:12.2"
msgid "puññatthassa jigīsato;"
msgstr "to someone who wants and needs merit,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.179:12.3"
msgid "Santesu paṭhamaṃ dinnā,"
msgstr "a teacher’s offering is abundant"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.179:12.4"
msgid "vipulā hoti dakkhiṇā."
msgstr "if given first to the peaceful ones."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.214"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "an5.179:13.1"
msgid "Santo have pavakkhāmi,"
msgstr "I will tell of the peaceful ones,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.179:13.2"
msgid "sāriputta suṇohi me;"
msgstr "Sāriputta, listen to me."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.179:13.3"
msgid "Iti kaṇhāsu setāsu,"
msgstr "Cows may be black or white,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.179:13.4"
msgid "rohiṇīsu harīsu vā."
msgstr "red or tawny,"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "an5.179:14.1"
msgid "Kammāsāsu sarūpāsu,"
msgstr "mottled or uniform,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.179:14.2"
msgid "gosu pārevatāsu vā;"
msgstr "or pigeon-colored."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.179:14.3"
msgid "Yāsu kāsuci etāsu,"
msgstr "But when one is born among them,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.179:14.4"
msgid "danto jāyati puṅgavo."
msgstr "the bull that’s tamed,"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "an5.179:15.1"
msgid "Dhorayho balasampanno,"
msgstr "—a behemoth, powerful,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.179:15.2"
msgid "kalyāṇajavanikkamo;"
msgstr "well-paced in pulling forward—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.179:15.3"
msgid "Tameva bhāre yuñjanti,"
msgstr "they yoke the load just to him,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.179:15.4"
msgid "nāssa vaṇṇaṃ parikkhare."
msgstr "regardless of his color."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "an5.179:16.1"
msgid "Evamevaṃ manussesu,"
msgstr "So it is for humans,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.179:16.2"
msgid "yasmiṃ kismiñci jātiye;"
msgstr "wherever they may be born,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.179:16.3"
msgid "Khattiye brāhmaṇe vesse,"
msgstr "—among aristocrats, brahmins, merchants,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.179:16.4"
msgid "sudde caṇḍālapukkuse."
msgstr "workers, or outcastes and scavengers—"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc17"></a>
msgctxt "an5.179:17.1"
msgid "Yāsu kāsuci etāsu,"
msgstr "but when one is born among them,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.179:17.2"
msgid "danto jāyati subbato;"
msgstr "tamed, true to their vows."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.179:17.3"
msgid "Dhammaṭṭho sīlasampanno,"
msgstr "Firm in principle, accomplished in ethical conduct,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.179:17.4"
msgid "saccavādī hirīmano."
msgstr "truthful, conscientious,"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc18"></a>
msgctxt "an5.179:18.1"
msgid "Pahīnajātimaraṇo,"
msgstr "they’ve given up birth and death,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.179:18.2"
msgid "brahmacariyassa kevalī;"
msgstr "and have completed the spiritual journey."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.179:18.3"
msgid "Pannabhāro visaṃyutto,"
msgstr "With burden put down, detached,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.179:18.4"
msgid "katakicco anāsavo."
msgstr "they’ve completed the task and are free of defilements."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc19"></a>
msgctxt "an5.179:19.1"
msgid "Pāragū sabbadhammānaṃ,"
msgstr "Gone beyond all things,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.179:19.2"
msgid "anupādāya nibbuto;"
msgstr "they’re extinguished by not grasping."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.179:19.3"
msgid "Tasmiñca viraje khette,"
msgstr "In that flawless field,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.179:19.4"
msgid "vipulā hoti dakkhiṇā."
msgstr "a teacher’s offering is abundant."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc20"></a>
msgctxt "an5.179:20.1"
msgid "Bālā ca avijānantā,"
msgstr "Fools who don’t understand"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.179:20.2"
msgid "dummedhā assutāvino;"
msgstr "—stupid, uneducated—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.179:20.3"
msgid "Bahiddhā dadanti dānāni,"
msgstr "give their gifts to those outside,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.179:20.4"
msgid "na hi sante upāsare."
msgstr "and don’t attend the peaceful ones."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc21"></a>
msgctxt "an5.179:21.1"
msgid "Ye ca sante upāsanti,"
msgstr "But those who do attend the peaceful ones"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.179:21.2"
msgid "sappaññe dhīrasammate;"
msgstr "—wise, esteemed as sages—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.179:21.3"
msgid "Saddhā ca nesaṃ sugate,"
msgstr "and whose faith in the Holy One"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.179:21.4"
msgid "mūlajātā patiṭṭhitā."
msgstr "has roots planted deep,"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc22"></a>
msgctxt "an5.179:22.1"
msgid "Devalokañca te yanti,"
msgstr "they go to the realm of the gods,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.179:22.2"
msgid "kule vā idha jāyare;"
msgstr "or are born here in a good family."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.179:22.3"
msgid "Anupubbena nibbānaṃ,"
msgstr "Gradually those astute ones"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.179:22.4"
msgid "adhigacchanti paṇḍitā”ti."
msgstr "reach extinguishment.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.179:22.5"
msgid "Navamaṃ."
msgstr ""
